<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910604-0042</DOCNO><DOCID>910604-0042.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Benton Oil andamp; Gas Co.:   Interest in Louisiana Field   Is Increased for $9.5 Million</HL><DATE>06/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BTN</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)</MS><IN>OIL DRILLING AND EXPLORATION (DRL)OIL EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)PETROLEUM (PET)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)LOUISIANA (LA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Benton Oil andamp; Gas Co. said it acquired an additional 13.3%working interest in the West Cote Blanche Bay Field inLouisiana from four private companies for about $9.5 million.   Benton, an oil and gas exploration and production company,said the acquisition brings its stake to a 42% workinginterest in the field.</LP><TEXT>   Terms call for a cash payment of about $500,000, shares ofBenton valued at about $1 million and mortgage notes for $8million. The notes are due in three equal installments inOctober 1991, and in January and April 1992. Benton issuedabout 95,000 shares as part of the transaction. Before theissuance, the company had a total of 9.4 million sharesoutstanding.   West Cote Blanche Bay currently produces about 2,000barrels of oil a day and two million cubic feet of naturalgas a day. The company said it expects production to increaseover the next few months as a result of a shallowdevelopmental oil well program that will start in June.</TEXT></DOC>